signatureAbility.signatureDescription: Players with this ability will recover from the effects of Wear and Tear and fatigue at an increased rate between plays.
Receivers with this ability catch more consistently while catching passes 10-20 yards from the LoS, inside the numbers
When lined up in the slot, receivers with this ability make faster cuts and have better hands when catching passes less than 10 yards from the LoS
Passers with this ability have increased throw power on bullet precision passes (except on high/low throws).
Passers with this ability have perfect accuracy on all throws inside the numbers (except on high/low throws).
Defenders with this ability have a chance to receive dominant bull rush wins when their stamina is full. This consumes additional stamina.
Defenders with this ability are granted a free pass rush move once per play after spending stamina to perform one
Defenders with this ability do not need to spend a point on shed attempts during a run play
Shutdown defenders have the talent to erase receivers from the game. When they enter the zone, their coverage is tighter and interceptions are more frequent on contested catches.
Players with this ability have an increased chance to catch passes that have been tipped into the air.
Players with this ability are more likely to succeed at and attempt diving catches and swats.
Defenders with this ability force more catch knockouts and react quicker in deep zone coverage, 20+ yards from the LoS and outside the hash marks.
Blockers with this ability reduce a rusher's chances of using a quick block shed move while pass blocking.
Blockers with this ability start every new blocking encounter with built-in resistance
Players with this ability can detect user-controlled defenders before the snap; as well as 3rd and 4th down blitzers. Can be bluffed.
Blockers with this ability will allow less frequent shed attempts by their block target
The game's top defenders excel in all situations. When they enter the zone, this ability increases their chance of defeating run blocks, and disrupting catches via tackles.
Players with this ability will recover from the effects of Wear and Tear and fatigue at an increased rate between plays.
Defenders with this ability will cause increased fatigue penalties when tackling a ballcarrier with a non-conservative tackle.
Defenders with this ability force more catch tackle knockouts in man-to-man versus short routes less than 10 yards from LoS
